@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<div class="container py-4">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p class="text-muted">Last updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM yyyy")</p>

    <p>
        This site is a personal software-engineering portfolio. It does not sell products and does
        not collect personal information for advertising.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">What is stored</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>An anonymous identifier cookie, so your saved searches, features, and collections persist between visits.</li>
        <li>If you sign in with Google, your name, email address, and profile picture are stored to identify your account.</li>
        <li>Standard server logs (request paths, timestamps, error details) for reliability and security.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
        Sign-in is handled by Google OAuth. Mapping, geocoding, and address features call Esri/ArcGIS
        services with the locations you enter. No data is sold or shared for advertising.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">Your choices</h2>
    <p>
        You can sign out at any time and delete your profile and associated data from your account
        page. Clearing your browser cookies removes the anonymous identifier.
    </p>

    <p>Questions? <a href="/#contact">Get in touch</a>.</p>
</div>
